cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for scientific information extraction. The paper introduces a multi-task setup for identifying and classifying entities, relations, and coreference clusters in scientific articles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses machine learning techniques, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also uses a unified framework called Scientific Information Extractor (SciIE), which is a machine learning model, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible category. The paper also deals with analyzing information in scientific literature, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible category. Finally, the paper uses a multi-task setup to reduce cascading errors between tasks, which makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category.
